notes: >
  Built per today's strategist plan (mail-merge-2026-06-27.md): two named-competitor
  "alternative" pages (Apollo.io, Gmelius), one head-to-head comparison (YAMM vs Mailmeteor),
  and one decision-stage how-to (drip campaign / sequence). All are root-level Jekyll .md
  with permalink:/slug/, single H1, top+bottom CTA to /mail-merge-for-gmail-and-sheets/
  (never GPT for Sheets), workflow steps, comparison tables on the alt/comparison pages,
  example template, internal links to existing pages, FAQ + FAQPage JSON-LD.
  Comparison/alternative pages carry visible non-affiliation disclaimers and dated/factual,
  non-defamatory claims (Apollo page explicitly states the product has no contact database
  or email verification). Sending/sequence pages include consent/deliverability cautions
  (permissioned contacts, test sends, Gmail/Workspace limits, unsubscribe).
  Post-build verification caught that {{first_name}}/{{company}} merge-field examples on the
  drip page were being consumed by Liquid (rendered empty); wrapped them in {% raw %} and
  rebuilt/redeployed (fix commit 83e869d), then confirmed they render literally live.
  Only the 4 intended page files (+ this marker) were staged/committed; unrelated untracked
  files from a concurrent GPT-for-Sheets builder (clay-alternative-*, *-google-sheets-ai.md,
  .claude/launch.json) were left untouched.
